    "However, Tang et al. (2022) found through research that recycling biological building materials can save land.",
    "This large space could be repurposed for other ecological or developmental uses, promoting efficient land use and management.",
    "In addition, gases with environmental impacts are emitted during the transport and transfer of biological materials, for example, filling cannabis-based panels releases 90% of carbon dioxide and 9% of methane during transport of about 30 km to a harmless storage facility (Schiavoni et al. 2016).",
